{
  "texts": [
    "• <MASK> returning, after having drunk their fill.",
    "• When <MASK> arrives at the spring, quite regardless of any spectator, he buries his head in the water above his eyes, and greedily swallows great mouthfuls, at the rate of about ten in a minute.",
    "Compute AnthroScore for each sentence, as per equation (1) on L211.",
    "This step is lexiconfree and does not depend on the choice of text or entity since we compare the probabilities of human vs. non-human pronouns replacing <MASK>.",
    "Then, we take the average AnthroScore across the three sentences as a measure of anthropomorphism of tortoises in this text."
